<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9657> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9657" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/10> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "ref. 439" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7290> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7290" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Monetalis. Crawford rightly identifies the monetalis with RE no. 232, who was quaestor in 48, not with no. 233, his son (as suggested with a query in MRR 2.437), who was pr. in 29 and cos. in 18, and dates his coinage to 50. In MRR 2.437, and Index, 554, read (232), and add Crawford,  RRC 1.460, no. 439, 50 B.C. On his quaestorship, MRR 2.274, 48 B.C., refer also to Oros. 6.15.19. See Sumner, Orators 93, 133, 143.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5641> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5641" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Commanded a portion of Caesar's fortifications about Dyrrachium at the point where Pompey attacked and inflicted serious losses (Caes. BC 3.62.4, and 64-65)." .
